original_title: Andrew Bailey: Bondi, Patel bring in Missouri AG to serve as FBI co-deputy director with Dan Bongino | CNN Politics
article_summary: Missouri Attorney General Andrew Bailey appointed as co-deputy director of the FBI, replacing Dan Bongino following a rift over the handling of Jeffrey Epstein files. Bailey, a decorated war veteran and former state attorney general, will serve alongside Bongino and FBI Director Kash Patel.</s>
